{
  "texts": [
    "Miller (2017) distinguishes between (causal) attributions and (causal) explanations.",
    "Attribution involves extracting relationships and causes, but it is not necessarily an explanation, even if a person could use attributions to derive their own explanation.",
    "Explanation also involves selecting, contextualizing, and presenting causes and relationships to the stakeholders.",
    "way that aligns with human cognitive biases and social expectations.",
    "In some sense, the output of interpretability methods is an attribution."
  ]
}